
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> How project has been configured
- $ npm init   : initialize node projetc
- $ npm install nodemon --save-dev  : install package nodemon, witch restart node server automaticaly after any saved file
nodemon is here only used for test in DEV environment, not in production.
source : https://techoverflow.net/2017/08/12/using-nodemon-without-a-global-installation/
- "mynodemon": "./node_modules/nodemon/bin/nodemon.js app.js" : this line was add to package.json. Aims to run mynodemon with npm
( see command below ) 
- $ npm install express --save-dev : install express package to create a simple http server
- create file app.js to be run, then getting a webserver
- 
- 


>>>>>>>>>>>>>> to lauch server 
$ npm run mynodemon



>>>>>>>>>>>>>> troubleshooting
- after pull from git, nothing happen when trying to run server
answer : .gitignore exclude node_modules directory. To install needed packages, use command : $ npm install